Article: Eva Unit production timeline
 think the construction period for these Units best fits midway between Unit 02 and Units 05-13, since I don't see much sense in NERV building Unit 02 and then suddenly waiting ten years to start the next batch. (As a fun but irrelevant side note, Shinji's pallet magnum from episode 16 is probably also a Second Branch product, as the original Desert Eagle design is American and the pistol was being made in the US when NGE was produced. Assuming that Israel flooded after Second Impact, it would still be made in the US in 2015.) Units 05 through 13: 2014-2015 The third-generation production model Evas are more or less MacGuffined into continuity during the End of Everything. Hyuga tells Misato that mass production had just begun at the time of episode 22, but I suspect that it had been going on as a camouflaged operation before that. Units 05 and 06 must have been known to NERV's Japanese branch already, as spare parts from them were being shipped to Japan for use on Unit 00, but they certainly weren't supposed to be done in time for the events of EoE. Units XX, XY and XZ: 2012-2015? As for the three Simulation Bodies attacked by the 12th Angel, I honestly have no idea. The best I can come up with is that they're fairly new, as the section of NERV HQ that houses them is mentioned as being of recent construction. Any suggestions? Well, that's everything I can remember and find from watching episodes 17 through 22'. If I've totally fumbled, hopefully one of ye olde veterans will straighten me out. Keep the flames below 200Â°, please. Apologies if this has been done before; I did a forum search but didn't find anything. So how long does it actually take to build an Eva? I assume that the process was streamlined as Gehirn / NERV progressed, but it must have taken years in the beginning and months by the time the MP Evas were made. There was something else I wanted to add, but now I can't remember what it was. I'll post it when it comes back to me.

